                            <p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>
                            <p style="text-align: center;"><a name="OldestJikokuten"></a><a href="../html/jikokuten.html"><img id="Picture2154" height="40" width="445" src="../assets/images/top-of-page-long.GIF" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="top" border="0" alt="Jump to Top of Page" title="Jump to Top of Page"></a></p>
                            <p style="text-align: left;"><i><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;"></span></i><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><i><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;"></span></i><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif; font-style: normal;">JYAKI (JAKI) DEMON - 邪鬼</span></span><i><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;"><br><span style="font-style: normal;">In Japan, the </span></span></i><a href="../html/shitenno.shtml"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif; font-style: normal;">Four Shitenn</span>ō<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif; font-style: normal;"> Guardians</span></a><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;"> are almost always shown stepping on evil demons called </span><a href="../html/shitenno.shtml#jyaki"><span style="font-family: '‚l‚r ‚oƒSƒVƒbƒN', monospace;"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;">Jyaki or Tent</span>ō<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;">ki</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;">. This iconography symbolizes the power of the </span><a href="../html/shitenno.shtml"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif; font-style: normal;">Shitenn</span>ō</a><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;"> to repel and defeat evil. </span></p>
                            <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="slideshows/tentoki1-hase-dera-kamakura.JPG" rel="lightbox" title="Tentoki or Jyaki, Hase Dera, Kamakura. Mid-late 20th century. Metal."><img id="Picture2159" height="110" width="147" src="../assets/images/autogen/tentoki1-TN-hase-dera-kamakura_1.jpg" vspace="2" hspace="0" align="top" border="0" alt="Tentoki at Hase Dera in Kamakura (metal statues)" title="Tentoki at Hase Dera in Kamakura (metal statues)" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0,0,0);"></a>&nbsp;<a href="slideshows/tentoki2-hase-dera-kamakura.JPG" rel="lightbox" title="Tentoki or Jyaki, Hase Dera, Kamakura. Mid-late 20th century. Metal."><img id="Picture2160" height="110" width="147" src="../assets/images/autogen/tentoki2-TN-hase-dera-kamakura.jpg" vspace="2" hspace="0" align="top" border="0" alt="Tentoki at Hase Dera in Kamakura (metal statues)" title="Tentoki at Hase Dera in Kamakura (metal statues)" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0,0,0);"></a> <a href="slideshows/tentoki3-hase-dera-kamakura.JPG" rel="lightbox" title="Tentoki or Jyaki, Hase Dera, Kamakura. Mid-late 20th century. Metal."><img id="Picture2161" height="110" width="147" src="../assets/images/autogen/tentoki3-TN-hase-dera-kamakura.jpg" vspace="2" hspace="0" align="top" border="0" alt="Tentoki at Hase Dera in Kamakura (metal statues)" title="Tentoki at Hase Dera in Kamakura (metal statues)" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0,0,0);"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;">Jaki (Jyaki) at Hase Dera in Kamakura (click any image to enlarge)<br>&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Sans-serif;"><a style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;" href="../html/shitenno.shtml#jyaki">Click here for more details about the Jyaki demons.</a></center></span></p>
