                            <p style="text-align: center;"><img id="Picture2124" height="325" width="400" src="../assets/images/autogen/shitenno-montage-horyuji-nara-W400-comprehensive-dictionary.jpg" vspace="3" hspace="0" align="top" border="1" alt="Click any image to jump to that deity's stand-alone page." title="Click any image to jump to that deity's stand-alone page." usemap="#map1" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0,0,0);"><map name="map1" id="map1"><area shape="rect" id="RectangleHotspot51" coords="6,0,97,317" href="../html/koumokuten.html"><area shape="rect" id="RectangleHotspot52" coords="108,3,202,318" href="../html/zouchoten.html"><area shape="rect" id="RectangleHotspot53" coords="216,2,296,318" href="../html/tamonten.html"><area shape="rect" id="RectangleHotspot54" coords="314,2,390,319" href="../html/jikokuten.html"></map><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;">Four Shitennō, Hōryūji Temple 法隆寺, Nara<br>Mid-7th Century. Oldest extant set of the four.<br>Kōmokuten 広目天, Zōchōten 増長天, Tamonten 多門天, Jikokuten 持国天<br>Painted Wood, Each Statue Approx. 133.5 cm in Height<br>Photos from Comprehensive Dictionary of Japan&#39;s Nat&#8217;l Treasures<br>国宝大事典 (西川 杏太郎. ISBN 4-06-187822-0.</span></p>
                            <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="../html/jikokuten.html"><img id="Picture733" height="40" width="445" src="../assets/images/top-of-page-long.GIF" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="top" border="0" alt="Jump to Top of Page" title="Jump to Top of Page"></a></p>
